    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Ek, En-o, Eq, Et). Stands from Yosemite National Park (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b, Taylor 1984, see Cheng 2004) and generally from the higher elevations in the section (Potter 2005) characterize the alliance.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Ptilagrostis kingii </i>stands are usually small and associated intimately with other wet and dry meadow vegetation types. Human-mediated shifts in the water table impact stands through increased erosion, which can result from cumulative effects of timber harvest and road construction. Potter (2005) also suggested that stands are susceptible to livestock trampling and overuse through compaction and loss of soil structure if grazed when wet. </div>
</div>

    

    

    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
